About Clio


At Clio, we are on a mission to transform the legal experience for all. As the world's leading provider of cloud-based legal software, we provide lawyers with low-barrier, affordable solutions to manage and grow their firms more effectively, more profitably, and with better client experiences. Through the cloud, we believe that we can help create a more inclusive legal community and a more equitable legal system.

We are an award-winning team that has been recognized as one of Canada’s Best Managed Companies , Canada’s Most Admired Cultures and has topped Fast Company’s list of Most Innovative Companies . In line with our mission, we’ve been up to some big things, including becoming a multi-product company, launching a $1 million COVID-19 Legal Relief Initiative , and most recently, securing a US$110M Series E funding round and a USD $1.6B valuation.

This is a historic moment in the growth of legal technology! As the first legal practice management unicorn globally, and one of only a handful of Canadian unicorns, this is only the beginning. If you’ve ever wanted to do the best work of your career, while having a meaningful impact in the lives of others, then Clio is the place for you.

 


HR Manager


 

The Inner City Health Associates (ICHA) is a group of approximately 200 physicians and nurses who predominantly provide short-term transitional health services to homeless or marginally housed people in Toronto. ICHA is funded by the Ontario Ministry of Health. We are a specialized service for high needs homeless individuals who are unable to access, or who face significant barriers to accessing, primary care or community psychiatric health care in other settings. We aim to transition client care to other community-based providers whenever possible. For more information about what we do, visit our website at: http://www.icha-toronto.ca.

 


Position Profile


The Human Resources (HR) Manager will provide strategic and operational leadership for ICHA’s human resource-related functions. The Human Resources Manager develops HR policies and initiatives and administers/leads all traditional HR functions, including labour relations.

 


Accountability


The HR Manager reports to the Director of Operations at Inner City Health Associates.

 


Roles and Responsibilities


The HR Manager will have primary accountability for the following activities:

 


Employee and Labour Relations



Act as a point person for ICHA staff to express their needs and concerns with regards to the work environment and act on staff feedback as appropriate;

Manage personnel-related issues and appropriately escalate as required to the Director of Operations or Medical Director for resolution;

Ongoing management, support and interpretation of any Collective Agreement;

Manage any employee issues for unionized staff in accordance with the provisions of the Collective Agreement;

Ensure continued compliance with applicable legislation and regulations; and

Maintain and update confidential personnel and legal files.


 


Policy Development and Implementation



Develop and implement new HR programs, policies and procedures;

Lead staff education regarding the implementation of new HR policies;

Update policies based on new legislation; and

Review and update all ICHA HR policies on a regular basis.


 


Payroll and Benefits Administration



Provide employees with benefits (health, dental, life insurance, and pension/RRSP plan) information and Employee Assistance Plan (EAP) information, and respond to inquiries;

Analyze, audit and complete administrative tasks related to the corporate benefits package &amp; pension/RRSP plan, including enrolling new staff;

Maintain and evolve HR processes and systems including scheduling, timesheet and time off tracking, preparing payroll summaries, Ceridian payroll support for staff, maintaining staff HR portal, and managing correspondence with staff on payroll issues;

Orient new staff to HR processes and tools;

Support clinical managers with creation of on-site weekly staff schedules;

Work with Finance department to support payroll process; and

Manage the sick leave and Long-Term Disability process.


 


Recruitment, Retention and Employee Orientation



Manage the talent acquisition process including obtaining hiring approvals, job postings, applicant screening, maintenance of applicant records, coordination of offering process and new hire set up;

Lead the delivery of New Hire Orientation and various training programs to all employees as required;

Issue and manage temporary employment contracts

Update job descriptions as required;

Play a leadership role in organizational training and development initiatives;

Coordinate all-staff meetings;

Plan and organize staff recognition events; and

Liaise with employees to understand their education and development needs.


 


Health and Safety



Liaise and collaborate with Occupational Health and Safety team on workplace health and safety policies, activities and initiatives;

Co-chair the Joint Health and Safety Committee;

Support employees training in health and safety programs, policies and procedures; and

Assist with implementing modified work for injured/sick workers.


 


Culture and change management



Develop, implement, and manage communication and change management tactics to ensure the sustainability of people-related initiatives, proactively engaging stakeholders in content, design and implementation;

Support strategic and operational planning, including leading periodic evaluation and refresh of organizational values;

Ongoing communications to staff on new initiatives, policies and programs, through email, presentations and newsletters; and

Design and lead organizational training and development initiatives.


 


Other


•        Perform other tasks as required by the Director of Operations


 



Qualifications &amp; Skills


 


Minimum of 4 years of progressively complex human resources generalist experience; management experience leading direct reports advantageous;

CHRP/CHRL or equivalent designation preferred;

Minimum two-year undergraduate degree;

Experience working in unionized environments and providing collective agreement interpretation, grievances, and arbitrations strongly preferred;

Ability to operate with the highest level of confidentiality and discretion;

Strong conflict resolution skills;

Demonstrated ability to multi-task in a fast paced environment and manage competing deadlines and periods of intense activity;

Proven success in staff development, employee counseling and coaching;

Ability to manage and influence change;

Strong influencing and interpersonal skills that can build credibility with clients based on your knowledge and collaborative style;

Superb written and verbal communication skills with the ability to present at the senior level;

Group facilitation skills;

Negotiation skills;

Experience in health care is an asset;

Self-directed with an ability to organize, plan, and prioritize;

Ability to work in a small organization as part of a committed team with fluidity in roles and responsibilities;

Open minded, non-judgmental with a commitment to upholding the rights and dignity of all people and respecting their diversity;

Inner City Health Associates requires that all employees are fully vaccinated against COVID-19 before beginning their employment with the organization.


 


Work Environment, Travel &amp; Salary



The position will be a hybrid in-person and remote role based at the Inner City Health Associate’s Office on 59 Adelaide St E, Toronto;

The position requires minimal physical effort;

37.5 hour work week;

Competitive salary between $ 90,000-$105,000 depending on experience and attractive benefits package


 


Start Date: Immediate



 



Inner City Health Associates is committed to developing an inclusive, barrier-free selection process and work environment. If contacted, please advise us if you require any accommodation measures to ensure you will be interviewed in a fair and equitable manner. Information received relating to accommodation requests will be treated with confidentiality.


 

